cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DC

The paper deals with spectrum trading in cognitive radio networks, which involves game theory and network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also involves networking and communication infrastructure, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper deals with cognitive radio networks, which suggests the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves contract theory and mathematical modeling, which suggests the category cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves simulations and modeling of network behavior, which suggests the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
